sentences: Nichelle Strong (born September 10, 1968), known by her stage name Nikki D is an American rapper.
Prior to releasing "Daddy's Little Girl", Strong was on tour in Europe for a year with fellow R&B artist Alyson Williams.
In 1998, Strong became the vice president of A&R at Flavor Unit Records, a position she held for two years.
Today she is the marketing manager at "Phat Fashions", the apparel company that houses Phat Farm, Baby Phat, and Atman.
